{"id":"int-15726b664921ec5fdf4f3587adffcd2c","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-06-04T05:20:03.824824Z","actor":"Victor De Simone","issue_id":"flow-bly","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Merged via PR #64 (squash). --auto runs now DEFER-AND-EXIT instead of parking: on a clarifying question/sub-90%/BAIL the run comments the questions on the ticket, sets it deferred (drops from bd ready, drainer stops relaunching), and exits. No more headless-park-forever. Took #3 (not the rejected PTY-doc #1). seam_check green."}}
{"id":"int-429a2bae738c446504ca259a37c0eca1","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-06-04T05:21:00.210069Z","actor":"Victor De Simone","issue_id":"flow-2cr","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Superseded by flow-bly (PR #64, merged). bly shipped the genuine fix: --auto runs DEFER-AND-EXIT (defer ticket in place + comment + exit, drops from bd ready). 2cr proposed the file-a-NEW-bead variant; defer-in-place is strictly better (no loop re-entry, no bead proliferation). Goal (drain never stalls on a park) achieved."}}
